{"path": "/data6/user24215463/Wan2.2/Wan2.2_SA3_fullrepo_fp16_edges_sagetriton_v0/qk_policy_high_noise_edges2_fp16.json", "kind": "file", "size": 192, "mtime": 1781244573, "head": "{\n  \"default\": \"hif4\",\n  \"fallback\": \"ref\",\n  \"high_noise\": {\n    \"self\": {\n      \"0-1\": \"ref\",\n      \"38-39\": \"ref\"\n    },\n    \"cross\": {\n      \"0-1\": \"ref\",\n      \"38-39\": \"ref\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}
{"path": "/data6/user24215463/Wan2.2/Wan2.2_SA3_fullrepo_fp16_edges_sagetriton_v0/qk_policy_edges2_fp16.json", "kind": "file", "size": 338, "mtime": 1781244573, "head": "{\n  \"default\": \"hif4\",\n  \"fallback\": \"ref\",\n  \"high_noise\": {\n    \"self\": {\n      \"0-1\": \"ref\",\n      \"38-39\": \"ref\"\n    },\n    \"cross\": {\n      \"0-1\": \"ref\",\n      \"38-39\": \"ref\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"low_noise\": {\n    \"self\": {\n      \"0-1\": \"ref\",\n      \"38-39\": \"ref\"\n    },\n    \"cross\": {\n      \"0-1\": \"ref\",\n      \"38-39\": \"ref\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}
{"path": "/data6/user24215463/Wan2.2/Wan2.2_SA3_fullrepo_fp16_edges_sagetriton_v0/QK_POLICY_IMPLEMENTATION.md", "kind": "file", "size": 11115, "mtime": 1781244573, "head": "# QK Policy Implementation Notes\n\nThis document records the QK pseudo-quantization policy implementation added for\nWan2.2 custom SDPA inference.\n\n## Goal\n\nThe implementation makes QK^T pseudo-quantization configurable per model phase,\nattention type, and transformer layer. It supports:\n\n- `hif4`: existing HiF4 pseudo-quantized QK path.\n- `nvfp4`: NVFP4 pseudo-quantized QK path.\n- `ref` / `bf16`: direct QK matmul without Q/K pseudo-quantization.\n- JSON policies for per-layer mode selection.\n- Runtime fallback from unstable Hif4 tiles.\n- Optional sampled calibration logs and compare-mode error metrics.\n\n## Changed Files\n\n- `generate.py`\n  - Added CLI arguments for QK mode, policy, fallback, guard, logging, and compare mode.\n  - Calls `configure_qk_policy(...)` at generation startup.\n\n- `wan/text2video.py`\n  - Annotates low/high noise models as `low_noise` and `high_noise`.\n  - Passes `model_role`, `timestep`, `timestep_idx`, and `cond_type` into model forward.\n\n- `wan/modules/model.py`\n  - Passes `quant_context` through `WanModel -> WanAttentionBlock -> WanSelfAttention/WanCrossAttention`.\n  - Adds `layer_idx` using `enumerate(self.blocks)`.\n  - Adds `attn_type` as `self` or `cross`."}
