{"path": "/data6/user24215463/Wan2.2/Wan2.2_SA3_fullrepo_fp16_edges_sagetriton_v0/ROWMAX_BUNDLE_MANIFEST.txt", "kind": "file", "size": 363, "mtime": 1781244573}
{"path": "/data6/user24215463/Wan2.2/Wan2.2_SA3_fullrepo_fp16_edges_sagetriton_v0/README_ROWMAX_SCALAR_PRESET.md", "kind": "file", "size": 907, "mtime": 1781244573, "head": "# Row-max scalar preset mode\n\nThis Wan2.2 package includes a small text preset file instead of requiring the original large `.pt` row-max profile.\n\nIncluded file:\n\n```bash\nrowmax_scalar_presets_stable_heads_offset_m10.txt\n```\n\nThe text file stores one scalar preset per selected stable head/timestep/branch/attention type:\n\n```text\nbranch attn timestep layer query_len key_len num_heads head preset_max\n```\n\n`preset_max` was generated as:\n\n```text\nmax(profile_row_max[head, :]) - 10\n```\n\nAt inference time:\n\n- heads listed in the txt use the scalar preset and skip runtime max search\n- heads missing from the txt still compute row max dynamically\n- no 16G `.pt` profile is needed\n\nBefore inference:\n\n```bash\nsource ./use_rowmax_stable_heads.sh\n```\n\nThen run your normal Wan `generate.py` command.\n\nCoverage:\n\n```text\n1051 / 1600 layer-heads = 65.6875%\n42040 / 64000 layer-head-timestep slots = 65.6875%\n```\n"}
